            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding the discharge of your patient, a 61-year-old male, admitted on 23/10/2024 following an injury to the medial collateral ligament (MCL) of the right knee. Clinical examination and MRI confirmed a significant MCL tear requiring surgical intervention. The patient underwent successful MCL repair under general anaesthesia on 24/10/2024. Post-operative recovery was uneventful, with satisfactory wound healing and adequate pain control achieved. Physiotherapy was initiated prior to discharge. He has been advised to continue outpatient physiotherapy, use crutches for mobilisation, and attend follow-up in our orthopaedic outpatient clinic in four weeks. Analgesia prescribed on discharge includes paracetamol and ibuprofen as required. Please do not hesitate to contact us should any concerns arise. Yours sincerely, Dr. [Treating Physician], Department of Orthopaedic Surgery.</div>"
            },
